		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<!-- wp:group {"align":"wide","style":{"spacing":{"padding":{"top":"var:preset|spacing|20","bottom":"var:preset|spacing|20","left":"var:preset|spacing|20","right":"var:preset|spacing|20"}}},"backgroundColor":"accent","layout":{"type":"constrained"}} -->
    <div class="wp-block-group alignwide has-accent-background-color has-background" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--20);padding-right:var(--wp--preset--spacing--20);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--20);padding-left:var(--wp--preset--spacing--20)"><!-- wp:paragraph -->
    <p>This is a private post. Only loggedin users will be able to see it normally. But with the <strong>Sharable Password Protected Posts</strong> plugin, you can also share them via a secret URL. This post has sharing via secret URL enabled, as you can see in the editor sidebar. </p>
    <!-- /wp:paragraph -->

    <!-- wp:paragraph -->
    <p>You can copy the secret URL form there as well. </p>
    <!-- /wp:paragraph -->

    <!-- wp:paragraph -->
    <p>To test this in WordPress Playground i, follow these steps:</p>
    <!-- /wp:paragraph -->

    <!-- wp:list {"ordered":true} -->
    <ol><!-- wp:list-item -->
    <li>Copy the secret URL</li>
    <!-- /wp:list-item -->

    <!-- wp:list-item -->
    <li>Click "View Post" on the top of the editor - which will open a new tab/window.</li>
    <!-- /wp:list-item -->

    <!-- wp:list-item -->
    <li>Log out of WordPress via the admin bar</li>
    <!-- /wp:list-item -->

    <!-- wp:list-item -->
    <li>Paste the secret link into the browsers address bar</li>
    <!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>
    <!-- /wp:list -->

    <!-- wp:paragraph -->
    <p>This shows you, how you can configure a post to share it privately.</p>
